a The young Lucullus's grandfather, Q. Servilius Caepio, was quaestor 100 B.C. and died 90 B.C. when Cicero was 16. But the following words seem to refer to a Caepio who, had he not died prematurely, would be in the prime of life when Cicero writes. This must mean the Caepio of the pre- ceding sentence, Lucullus's uncle, who may well have left Cicero as the guardian of his son, as is stated below.
